commit_msg: Fix checkstyle error again

Various improvements to K frontend #306

* generic -PROGRAM-PARSING not just for ID

* expand macros in llvm backend

* expand macros in haskell backend

* support or patterns in K frontend

* fix associativity of #Or and #And

* add tests for lambda

* document new behavior of ==K and =/=K

* allow unbound vars on rhs of ==K and =/=K

* resolve ==K and =/=K to lambdas

* change syntax of pattern matching operator

* fix bug in classpath

* update syntax of ml primitives in K

* fix copyright

* fix indent

* fix bug with formatter and polymorphic associative klabels

* update llvm submodule

* or patterns in ocaml backend

* add tests for or patterns

* add tests for or patterns

* fix syntax again

* use only minimal productions when creating ambiguities during unparsing

This solves an OutOfMemoryError when unparsing large associative lists
of polymorphic productions which were exploding in the size of the tree
during unparsing. We should never need to choose something that is not
minimal with respect to the overload relation because a minimal
production can always go anywhere a production would go that is greater
than it.

* check well sortedness when constructing tree nodes

* fix bug where extension module was not used to unparse collection items

* update test outputs

* update to k exercises

* fix bug with empty amb node

update substitution module to use KVar and hook #316

* update substitution module to use KVar and hook

* fix whitespace
added ImageMessageTests applied small fixes
added ImageMessageTests applied small fixes
fixed some typos and added ImageMessage functionality
debug
Adding db connection error message and some exception handling

ground markers: Fix startup and shutdown bug

When logging in to the game with the plugin disabled enabling it will
not cause points to be filled as the game state trigger will not be
reached. This commit properly loads points on plugin startup and clears
them on shutdown.
